		<title>17COMMUNICATIONS (CONTINUED)</title>
		<content> At the Sheffield office all the       
 letters are sorted by machine. Even   
 the second class mail which is sent to
 the Barnsley office is bagged up and  
 taken to Sheffield because it is      
 sorted much quicker there. We were    
 told of the importance of using the   
 post code here. Mr Young looked rather
 sad when he told us about the shift   
 of work from Barnsley to Sheffield and
 said that it was 'a sign of the       
 times'.                               
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
